article.headline: Pierre and Belmont defeat Lipscomb 80-79
article.description: — Jonathan Pierre led Belmont with 20 points and Isaiah Walker secured the victory when he converted a three-point play with three seconds left as the Bruins knocked off Lipscomb 80-79 on Tuesday night.

article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- — Jonathan Pierre led Belmont with 20 points and Isaiah Walker secured the victory when he converted a three-point play with three seconds left as the Bruins knocked off Lipscomb 80-79 on Tuesday night. Pierre added 10 rebounds for the Bruins (2-1). Carter Whitt scored 13 points and added six assists. Sam Orme and Drew Scharnowski both had 12 points. Jacob Ognacevic led the way for the Bisons (2-2) with 28 points, seven rebounds and four assists. Will Pruitt added 20 points, five assists and three steals for Lipscomb. Dylan Faulkner finished with 12 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
